The '''2011 OFC U-20 Championship''', was the 18th [[OFC Under 20 Qualifying Tournament]], the biennial [[Association football|football]] championship of Oceania ([[Oceania Football Confederation|OFC]]). It was held in [[Auckland]], [[New Zealand]] from 21 to 29 April 2011. The winner qualified for the [[2011 FIFA U-20 World Cup]]. Holders [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]] failed to qualify for this tournament. [[New Zealand national under-20 football team|New Zealand]] won this years edition.

==Participating teams==
{{details|2011 OFC U-20 Championship squads}}

